ibIfMIB.name: ibIfMIB

Supplementary information may be available on http://www.ietf.org/copyrights/ianamib.html. This module contains managed object definitions for managing InfiniBand interfaces.

ibIfPortStatTable.name: ibIfPortStatTable
ibIfPortStatTable.description: This table provides detail statistics for all InfiniBand interfaces attached to a particular system. There will be one row in this table for each InfiniBand interface in the system.

ibIfPortStatEntry.name: ibIfPortStatEntry
ibIfPortStatEntry.description: Statistics for a particular interface to an InfiniBand medium.

ibIfPortStatIfIndex.name: ibIfPortStatIfIndex
ibIfPortStatIfIndex.description: The ifIndex value of the InfiniBand interface to which these port statistics apply.

ibIfPortSymbolErrs.name: ibIfPortSymbolErrs
ibIfPortSymbolErrs.reference: InfiniBand Architecture Release 1.2 Vol. 1. Section 16.1.3.5; Table 225 PortCounters::SymbolErrorCounter.
ibIfPortSymbolErrs.description: Total number of minor link errors detected on one or more physical lanes.

ibIfPortLinkErrRecovery.name: ibIfPortLinkErrRecovery
ibIfPortLinkErrRecovery.reference: InfiniBand Architecture Release 1.2 Vol. 1. Section 16.1.3.5; Table 225 PortCounters::LinkErrorRecoveryCounter.
ibIfPortLinkErrRecovery.description: Total number of times the Port Training state machine has successfully completed the link error recovery process.

ibIfPortLinkDowned.name: ibIfPortLinkDowned
ibIfPortLinkDowned.reference: InfiniBand Architecture Release 1.2 Vol. 1. Section 16.1.3.5; Table 225 PortCounters::LinkDownedCounter.
ibIfPortLinkDowned.description: Total number of times the Port Training state machine has failed the link error recovery process and downed the link.

ibIfPortStatLocalPhyErrs.name: ibIfPortStatLocalPhyErrs
ibIfPortStatLocalPhyErrs.reference: InfiniBand Architecture Release 1.2 Vol. 1. Section 16.1.3.5; Table 225 PortCounters::PortRcvErrors.
ibIfPortStatLocalPhyErrs.description: Total number of packets received on the port that contain local physical errors (ICRC, VCRC, FCCRC, and all physical errors that cause entry into the BAD PACKET or BAD PACKET DISCARD states of the packet receiver state machine).

ibIfPortStatMalPktErrs.name: ibIfPortStatMalPktErrs
ibIfPortStatMalPktErrs.reference: InfiniBand Architecture Release 1.2 Vol. 1. Section 16.1.3.5; Table 225 PortCounters::PortRcvErrors.
ibIfPortStatMalPktErrs.description: Total number of packets received on the port that contain malformed packet errors - data packets: LVer, length, VL - link packets: operand, length, VL

ibIfPortStatRcvRemPhyErrs.name: ibIfPortStatRcvRemPhyErrs
ibIfPortStatRcvRemPhyErrs.reference: InfiniBand Architecture Release 1.2 Vol. 1. Section 16.1.3.5; Table 225 PortCounters::PortRcvRemotePhysicalErrors.
ibIfPortStatRcvRemPhyErrs.description: Total number of packets marked with the EBP delimiter received on the port.

ibIfPortStatRcvConstrErrs.name: ibIfPortStatRcvConstrErrs
ibIfPortStatRcvConstrErrs.reference: InfiniBand Architecture Release 1.2 Vol. 1. Section 16.1.3.5; Table 225 PortCounters::PortRcvConstraintErrors.
ibIfPortStatRcvConstrErrs.description: Total number of packets received on the port that are discarded for the following reasons: - FilterRawInbound is true and packet is raw - PartitionEnforcementInbound is true and packet fails partition key check or IP version check.

ibIfPortStatInactDiscards.name: ibIfPortStatInactDiscards
ibIfPortStatInactDiscards.reference: InfiniBand Architecture Release 1.2 Vol. 1. Section 16.1.4.2; Table 229 PortXmitDiscardDetails::PortInactiveDiscards.
ibIfPortStatInactDiscards.description: Total number of outbound packets discarded by the port because it is not in the active state.

ibIfPortStatNeighMTUDiscards.name: ibIfPortStatNeighMTUDiscards
ibIfPortStatNeighMTUDiscards.reference: InfiniBand Architecture Release 1.2 Vol. 1. Section 16.1.4.2; Table 229 PortXmitDiscardDetails::PortNeighborMTUDiscards.
ibIfPortStatNeighMTUDiscards.description: Total number of outbound packets discarded by the port because packet length exceeded the neighbor MTU.

ibIfPortStatSwLifetimeDiscards.name: ibIfPortStatSwLifetimeDiscards
ibIfPortStatSwLifetimeDiscards.reference: InfiniBand Architecture Release 1.2 Vol. 1. Section 16.1.4.2; Table 229 PortXmitDiscardDetails::PortSwLifetimeLimitDiscards.
ibIfPortStatSwLifetimeDiscards.description: Total number of outbound packets discarded by the port because the Switch Lifetime Limit was exceeded. Note this object is only incremented for switches.

ibIfPortStatHOQLifetimeDiscards.name: ibIfPortStatHOQLifetimeDiscards
ibIfPortStatHOQLifetimeDiscards.reference: InfiniBand Architecture Release 1.2 Vol. 1. Section 16.1.4.2; Table 229 PortXmitDiscardDetails::PortSwHOQLimitDiscards.
ibIfPortStatHOQLifetimeDiscards.description: Total number of outbound packets discarded by the port because the switch HOQ lifetime was exceeded. Note this object is only incremented for switches.

ibIfPortStatLinkIntergrityErrs.name: ibIfPortStatLinkIntergrityErrs
ibIfPortStatLinkIntergrityErrs.reference: InfiniBand Architecture Release 1.2 Vol. 1. Section 16.1.3.5; Table 225 PortCounters::LocalLinkIntegrityErrors.; Also see Table 145 PortInfo.
ibIfPortStatLinkIntergrityErrs.description: The number of times that the count of local physical errors exceeded the LocalPhyErrors threshold.

ibIfPortStatExcBufOverrunErrs.name: ibIfPortStatExcBufOverrunErrs
ibIfPortStatExcBufOverrunErrs.reference: InfiniBand Architecture Release 1.2 Vol. 1. Section 16.1.3.5; Table 225 PortCounters::ExcessiveBufferOverrunErrors.; Also see Table 145 PortInfo.
ibIfPortStatExcBufOverrunErrs.description: The number of times that OverrunErrors consecutive flow control update periods occurred with at least one overrun error in each period.

ibIfPortStatVL15Dropped.name: ibIfPortStatVL15Dropped
ibIfPortStatVL15Dropped.reference: InfiniBand Architecture Release 1.2 Vol. 1. Section 16.1.3.5; Table 225 PortCounters::VL15Dropped.
ibIfPortStatVL15Dropped.description: Number of incoming VL15 packets dropped due to resource limitations on the selected port (e.g., lack of buffers).

ibIfVLTrafficTable.name: ibIfVLTrafficTable
ibIfVLTrafficTable.description: This table provides traffic statistics for all virtual lanes that are configured on an InfiniBand interface. There will always be at least one data virtual lane in the range VL0-VL14 configured on an interface, as well as control channel VL15. Configuration of what VLs are available on a particular interface is done by IBA native management.

ibIfVLTrafficEntry.name: ibIfVLTrafficEntry
ibIfVLTrafficEntry.description: Information about a particular virtual lane (VL).

ibIfVLTrafficIfIndex.name: ibIfVLTrafficIfIndex
ibIfVLTrafficIfIndex.description: The ifIndex value of the InfiniBand interface to which these virtual lane (VL) traffic statistics apply.

ibIfVLIndex.name: ibIfVLIndex
ibIfVLIndex.description: Identifies what Virtual Lane (VL) instance is being addressed.

ibIfVLOutOctets.name: ibIfVLOutOctets
ibIfVLOutOctets.reference: InfiniBand Architecture Release 1.2 Vol. 1. Section 16.1.3.3; Table 223 CounterSelect::PortXmitDataVL.
ibIfVLOutOctets.description: The number of octets transmitted in valid data packets on this interface, including the START and END delimiters and the VCRC for this VL.

ibIfVLOutPkts.name: ibIfVLOutPkts
ibIfVLOutPkts.reference: InfiniBand Architecture Release 1.2 Vol. 1. Section 16.1.3.3; Table 223 CounterSelect::PortXmitPktVL.
ibIfVLOutPkts.description: The number of packets successfully sent on this VL.

ibIfVLInOctets.name: ibIfVLInOctets
ibIfVLInOctets.reference: InfiniBand Architecture Release 1.2 Vol. 1. Section 16.1.3.3; Table 223 CounterSelect::PortRcvDataVL.
ibIfVLInOctets.description: The number of octets in valid data packets received on this interface, including the START and END delimiters and the VCRC for this VL.

ibIfVLInPkts.name: ibIfVLInPkts
ibIfVLInPkts.reference: InfiniBand Architecture Release 1.2 Vol. 1. Section 16.1.3.3; Table 223 CounterSelect::PortRcvPktVL.
ibIfVLInPkts.description: The number of packets successfully received on this VL. This does not include link packets, since link packets are generated by the interface layer, and are not passed from any higher layer protocol.

ibIpoibLinkLayerAddrTable.name: ibIpoibLinkLayerAddrTable
ibIpoibLinkLayerAddrTable.description: This table contains information about all IPOIB link layer addresses associated with this InfiniBand interface (port).

ibIpoibLinkLayerAddrEntry.name: ibIpoibLinkLayerAddrEntry
ibIpoibLinkLayerAddrEntry.description: Information about specific IPOIB link layer addresses associated with this InfiniBand interface (port).

ibIpoibLinkLayerIfIndex.name: ibIpoibLinkLayerIfIndex
ibIpoibLinkLayerIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the IPOIB InfiniBand interface (port).

ibIpoibLinkLayerIndex.name: ibIpoibLinkLayerIndex
ibIpoibLinkLayerIndex.description: Index of the IPOIB Link Layer address in the table.

ibIpoibLinkLayerAddr.name: ibIpoibLinkLayerAddr
ibIpoibLinkLayerAddr.description: A Client Identifier for this interface (port). An implementation may associate multiple IPOIB interfaces on the same port. It is up to the implementation to ensure a unique Client Identifier when multiple IPOIB interfaces are defined over the same port and same GID. A unique, invariant interface-id value must be included in addition to the GID within the Client Identifier definition to achieve this. Note: a port may also be associated with multiple GIDs. Therefore, multiple IPOIB interfaces may exist on the same port while using a different GID from among the GIDs associated with the port. In either case, the IbIpoibLinkLayerAddr MUST be unique.

ibIfBasicCompliance.name: ibIfBasicCompliance
ibIfBasicCompliance.description: The basic implementation requirements for managed network entities that have InfiniBand network interfaces.

ibIfFullCompliance.name: ibIfFullCompliance
ibIfFullCompliance.description: The full implementation requirements for managed network entities that have InfiniBand network interfaces.

ibIfStatMandatoryPortStatGroup.name: ibIfStatMandatoryPortStatGroup
ibIfStatMandatoryPortStatGroup.description: Detailed error statistics group for mandatory InfiniBand-based Port Statistics counters.

ibIfStatOptionalPortStatGroup.name: ibIfStatOptionalPortStatGroup
ibIfStatOptionalPortStatGroup.description: Detailed error statistics group for optional InfiniBand-based Port Statistics counters.

ibIfVLTrafficGroup.name: ibIfVLTrafficGroup
ibIfVLTrafficGroup.description: Detailed per VL traffic statistics group.

ibIpoibLinkAddrGroup.name: ibIpoibLinkAddrGroup
ibIpoibLinkAddrGroup.description: Detailed per port IPOIB link layer address group.
